CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 5, 1955, page 21 reads: "Farrell Stalwarts - Two of the key figures in Farrell High School's drive for its second state high school cage championship are pictured above with their coach, Eddie McCluskey. On the left is Charley Kemp, and on the right is Jim McCoy. Both were regulars last season. McCoy was an all-state selection. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Two Farrell High School basketball players, Charley Kemp on left and Jim McCoy on right, wearing light colored uniform with "Farrell 14" across chest, standing on either side of their coach, Eddie McCluskey, in locker room with bench, chalkboard, and poster that reads "Ked's Bulletin"
